The paper deals with image processing tasks involving different image modalities, such as RGB images, infrared images, or multi-spectral images. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach based on joint sparse representations induced by coupled dictionaries, which involves learning a set of dictionaries that couple different image modalities in the sparse feature domain. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Moreover, the paper deals with multimodal images, which could also place it in the multimodal learning (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the presence of noise and the need for robustness, which could suggest that it belongs to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
